{
  "text": "We have to do with CQT Hopf * -algebra iff R(y * ⊗ x * ) = R(x ⊗ y), x, y ∈ B, iff q = 1 and b ∈ R. We have cotriangular (CT) Hopf algebra iff (R vz ) −1 = R zv for all v, z ∈ Rep G iff q = 1 and b = 0 (so then it is also a CT Hopf * -algebra). Using the above results, universal enveloping algebras for quantum Poincaré groups are introduced. Their commutation relations are investigated. Moreover, we classify C(Q)T Hopf ( * -)algebra structures for quantum Lorentz groups. We also show some general statements concerning coquasitriangularity. The results of [CITATION_1] are used in Section 5 of [CITATION_2] to define the Fock space for non-interacting particles of spin 0 on a quantum Minkowski space.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "15680993",
    "[CITATION_2]": "17836475"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "17836475": {
      "title": "Solutions of Klein-Gordon and Dirac equations on quantum Minkowski spaces",
      "abstract": "Covariant differential calculi and exterior algebras on quantum homogeneous spaces endowed with the action of inhomogeneous quantum groups are classified. In the case of quantum Minkowski spaces they have the same dimensions as in the classical case. Formal solutions of the corresponding Klein-Gordon and Dirac equations are found. The Fock space construction is sketched."
    },
    "15680993": {
      "title": "Quasitriangularity and enveloping algebras for inhomogeneous quantum groups",
      "abstract": "Coquasitriangular universal R matrices on quantum Lorentz and quantum Poincare groups are classified. The results are extended (under certain assumptions) to inhomogeneous quantum groups. Enveloping algebras on those objects are described."
    }
  }
}